be what you need

Somehow, Student Government Board man-
aged to convince three bigwig administrators to
listen to student concerns. In fact, they’re the
three administrators whose departments have the
most direct inﬂuence on students’ lives.

The heads of Student Health Services, Food
Services and Housing will all be present at
SGB’s Town Hall Meeting tonight to ﬁeld ques-

- tions and listen to students’ concerns.

SGB ought to be applauded for this achieve-
ment, because convincing administrators and
business people to listen to the public is no easy
task. But the battle is still only half won.

Students’ concerns will only be addressed if
students show up to present them. ’

